{
  "texts": [
    "In sparse lattice (ϕ ≲ 0.35), particle diffusivity lowers as ϕ increases, consistent with one's intuition.",
    "At high packing fractions (ϕ ≳ 0.35), however, D eff drastically increases as ϕ increases.",
    "We further compare the diffusion behavior of CAPs with ABPs.",
    "Figure 5c shows no significant difference in D eff (ϕ) for ABPs diffusing in the two types of lattices, in contrast to the distinct diffusion of CAPs.",
    "Moreover, D eff (ϕ) monotonically decreases for ABPs due to stronger caging at higher ϕ (Fig. 5c)."
  ]
}